h1.font: Commencing the Data Analysis of Your Project

p.font: n the initial step, it is essential to gather your raw RCC files along with your clinical data table in a text format. These two inputs represent the sole required files for your analysis.

p.font: In this step, a variety of Supervised Learning techniques are employed for binary classification, aiming to categorise the normalised data into distinct groups or classes based on gene expression profiles. The primary objective of utilising these techniques is to uncover hidden patterns within the data and construct a model capable of accurately classifying similar, yet unclassified data. This step is instrumental in interpreting your dataset.
